    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-03-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                        </placeName> (<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1909-03-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1909-03-17T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>)<lb/>(Received
                        March 18, 1909).</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is important, and perhaps decisive for ratification, that the Panama minister
                    and the Colombian minister exchange notes defining limits of Jurado. Opposition
                    is also laying stress on ambiguity sixth article of the treaty with the United
                    States, caused by placing the comma after “Refucio” instead of “Comercio.”</p>
                <p>Minister for foreign affairs of Colombia requests me to ask authorization to hold
                    myself in readiness to write a note saying that use conceded is understood to be
                    only as that right of refuge recognized by international law, to be subject to
                    the usages established by international law with regard to right of refuge, and
                    not as involving any breach of Colombian sovereignty over her ports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
